  "body": "If you create an empty project, and place this file in `contracts/test.sol`\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract C {\r\n  string public constant arbitraryString =\r\n      \"one\"\r\n      \"two\"\r\n      \"three\"\r\n      \"four\"\r\n      \"five\"\r\n      \"six\"\r\n      \"seven\"\r\n      \"eight\"\r\n      \"nine\";\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nhardhat will never finish compiling it, nor event get to invoke `solc`.\r\n\r\nHere are my logs\r\n\r\n```\r\n% hh compile --verbose\r\n  hardhat:core:config Loading Hardhat config from /private/tmp/npmproject-0/hardhat.config.js +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:global-dir Looking up Client Id at /Users/pato/Library/Application Support/hardhat-nodejs/analytics.json +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:global-dir Client Id found: REDACTED +1ms\r\n  hardhat:core:analytics Sending hit for /task/builtin +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:analytics Hit payload: REDACTED +1ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Creating HardhatRuntimeEnvironment +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile +1ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:get-compilation-tasks +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:solidity +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:solidity:get-source-paths +0ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:solidity:get-source-names +10ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:solidity:get-dependency-graph +2ms\r\n  hardhat:core:hre Running task compile:solidity:read-file +0ms\r\n```\r\n\r\nand it eventually runs out of memory and v8 crashes.\r\n\r\nI think this is a bug in the parser. wdyt, @fvictorio ?",
